Implement tools in `src/tools/issues.ts`:

## Tools to Implement

1. **ready** - Find ready issues/specs
   - CLI: `sg ready --json [--limit] [--priority] [--assignee] [--specs] [--issues]`

2. **list_issues** - List with filters
   - CLI: `sg issue list --json [--status] [--type] [--priority] [--assignee] [--limit]`

3. **show_issue** - Show details
   - CLI: `sg issue show <id> --json`

4. **create_issue** - Create new issue
   - CLI: `sg issue create "<title>" --json [--description] [--type] [--priority] [--assignee] [--parent] [--tags] [--estimate]`

5. **update_issue** - Update existing
   - CLI: `sg issue update <id> --json [--status] [--priority] [--assignee] [--type] [--title] [--description]`

6. **close_issue** - Close issues
   - CLI: `sg issue close <ids...> --json [--reason]`

7. **blocked_issues** - Get blocked items
   - CLI: `sg blocked --json [--specs] [--issues]`

## Implementation Pattern

```typescript
export async function ready(
  client: SudographClient,
  params: ReadyParams
): Promise<ReadyResult> {
  const args = ['ready'];
  if (params.limit) args.push('--limit', params.limit.toString());
  if (params.priority !== undefined) args.push('--priority', params.priority.toString());
  if (params.assignee) args.push('--assignee', params.assignee);
  if (params.show_specs) args.push('--specs');
  if (params.show_issues) args.push('--issues');

  return client.exec(args);
}
```

